Que 1) What are HTML Elements?
-------------------------------
HTML elements are the building blocks of a web page. 🧱
Every web page is made using many HTML elements.
An HTML element has 3 parts:
Opening Tag – tells the browser where the element starts
Content – the text or data inside the element
Closing Tag – tells the browser where the element ends
Example
<p>Interview Happy</p>
Explanation:
<p> → Opening tag
Interview Happy → Content
</p> → Closing tag
So the complete element is:
<p>Interview Happy</p>
Que 2) What is a Tag?
------------------------
A Tag is only the keyword inside < > brackets.
Example:
<p>      → Opening Tag
</p>     → Closing Tag
Tags do not contain content.
They only mark the start or end of an element.
3️⃣ Difference Between Element and Tag
Tag	Element
Part of HTML code	Complete structure
Written inside < >	Includes tag + content
Example: <p>	Example: <p>Hello</p>
Simple Example
Tag:
<p>
</p>
Element:
<p>Hello</p>
✅ One-line interview answer
HTML elements are the building blocks of web pages and consist of a start tag, content, and an end tag. A tag is
only the opening or closing part of an element.

Que 3)What is HTML?
-------------------
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard language used to create web pages. 🌐
It tells the browser how to display content like:
Text,Images,Links,Videos,Tables
Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>My Page</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Hello World</h1>
<p>This is my first webpage</p>
</body>
</html>
Here HTML uses tags to structure the page.
Que 4)Difference Between HTML and HTML5?
----------------------------------------
HTML	HTML5
Older version of HTML	Latest version
Limited multimedia support	Built-in audio & video support
Needs plugins like Flash	No plugins needed
Fewer semantic tags	New semantic tags added
Less support for mobile apps	Better for mobile applications
Example of New HTML5 Tags
<header>
<footer>
<section>
<article>
<nav>
These make the website more organized and readable.
3️⃣ Advantages of HTML5
1️⃣ Multimedia Support
HTML5 supports audio and video without plugins.
Example
<video controls>
<source src="movie.mp4">
</video>
2️⃣Better for Mobile Devices 📱
HTML5 works well on phones, tablets, and modern browsers.
3️⃣ New Semantic Tags
Tags like:
<header>
<footer>
<article>
make code clean and easy to understand.
4️⃣ Offline Storage
HTML5 can store data in the browser using:
Local Storage
Session Storage
5️⃣ Faster Performance ⚡
HTML5 pages load faster and smoother.
✅ Simple Interview Answer (Best)
HTML is the standard language used to create web pages.
HTML5 is the latest version of HTML that supports multimedia, new semantic tags, better performance, and mobile-friendly 
features.

